		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yep, we got it backwards. As <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Mirroring#Vertical" class="postlink">the wiki puts it</a>: "A horizontal arrangement of the nametables results in vertical mirroring [...] On cartridge boards made by Nintendo, this is selected by shorting the 'H' solder pad (for 'horizontal arrangement')." I guess that's why they call it "reverse" engineering <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
